### L3 — Fork: Create a parallel branch for A/B exploration
### SPEC §8.7
### Use case: the agent has two promising approaches to a problem.
### Fork from the current checkpoint; explore both independently.

POST /v1/sbp/sessions/a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890/fork HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your-api-key>

{
  "label": "Budget route via Seoul layover"
}

### Response — HTTP 201
### The fork shares all history through the fork point.
### Both sessions diverge independently from here.

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fork_session_id":    "a7b8c9d0-e1f2-3456-abcd-567890123456",
  "fork_session_token": "tok_fork_budget123",
  "fork_label":         "Budget route via Seoul layover",
  "origin_session_id":  "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "fork_point_step":    12
}
